#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
TwoTower-Sovereign — P2 SCALED: the DECISIVE pure-SSM-context ablation.

The n=20 run (train_p2_real.py) was INCONCLUSIVE on the trained denoiser (real≈shuffled
on the FIT set, no held-out generalization) — BUT a leave-one-out 1-NN probe CONFIRMED the
signal is present in the raw SSM context: the nearest-context neighbor shared 12.5% of block
tokens vs 3.8% for a random pair = 3.3x above chance. So the pure-SSM context DOES carry
continuation signal; the bottleneck was a 2-layer denoiser on only 20 prompts.

This script scales BOTH axes and runs the decisive verdict, reusing train_p2_real's structure
VERBATIM (the buleyean complement-KL + rejection-contrast loss, the E8-lattice/gate rejection
ledger, the mctx context extraction, the three-way ablation) and changing only:
  * DATA:   ~256 diverse short prompts (was 20), paired {SSM context, greedy K=8 continuation}.
  * PROBE:  a CHEAP dual (kernel/1-NN, n<<d) information-presence probe on the LARGER dataset —
            per-position held-out accuracy vs chance + the block-agreement scaling vs the 3.3x
            n=20 baseline. Run BEFORE the expensive train (it is the information-presence floor).
  * DENOISER: scaled toward the P1 spec (d_model=768, 4 layers, 8 heads) with AdamW weight
            decay + early-stop on held-out — bigger than the n=20 toy's 2-layer.
  * VERDICT: the DECISIVE metric is HELD-OUT (unseen prompts) recon-acc / per-token block
            agreement for REAL vs ZERO vs SHUFFLED. REAL > shuffled≈zero on HELD-OUT =
            pure-SSM-context thesis VINDICATED at scale. real≈shuffled≈zero = the denoiser
            still can't use it (reported honestly, with the probe as the information floor).

Run:  python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_scaled.py            # offline, uses cache
      python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_scaled.py --extract  # re-hit the mctx canary
      python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_scaled.py --small    # smoke on the n=20 cache
"""

